The **origami dove** is a traditional paper folding model representing **peace, hope, and harmony**.\
Although similar to the famous origami crane, the dove has a softer and more rounded silhouette.

This model is commonly folded using the **bird base**, a fundamental structure in origami used for many classic birds.

---

## History

The dove became a global symbol of peace in the 20th century after the artwork created by **Pablo Picasso**, which was used as the emblem for the **World Peace Congress 1949**.

Because of this symbolism, the origami dove is often used in peace events, educational activities, and cultural demonstrations.

